Package: treefarmr
Type: Package
Title: Tree-based Fast and Accurate Rule Set Models with Log-Loss and Probabilities
Version: 0.3.0
Author: TreeFARMR Development Team
Maintainer: TreeFARMR Development Team <treefarmr@example.com>
Description: R implementation of TreeFARMS (Tree-based Fast and Accurate Rule Set Models),
    providing optimal decision tree learning with support for log-loss optimization and 
    probability predictions. TreeFARMS finds optimal decision trees using either 
    misclassification loss or log-loss (cross-entropy), and provides well-calibrated 
    probability estimates bounded away from 0 and 1. This package uses direct Rcpp 
    bindings to the integrated C++ implementation, eliminating external dependencies 
    for easier distribution and better performance.
License: MIT
Depends: R (>= 3.6.0)
Imports: Rcpp (>= 1.0.0), jsonlite (>= 1.7.0)
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppParallel
Suggests: testthat, knitr, rmarkdown
SystemRequirements: C++11, GMP (GNU Multiple Precision Arithmetic Library)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
